  "prompt": "Why mobile phone is also know as cell phone?",
  "response": "The term **\"cell phone\"** is derived from the concept of **cellular technology**, which is the foundation of how modern mobile networks operate. Here's why the term \"cell phone\" is used:\n\n1. **Cellular Network Structure**:  \n   Mobile networks are divided into small geographic areas called **\"cells.\"** Each cell is served by a **base station** (cell tower), which handles communication for all the devices within that area. This division allows for efficient use of limited radio frequencies and ensures seamless coverage as users move from one cell to another.\n\n2. **Evolution of the Term**:  \n   Early mobile communication systems were designed around this cellular concept, leading to the term **\"cellular phone\"** or **\"cell phone.\"** Over time, \"cell phone\" became a common shorthand for mobile phones.\n\n3. **Technical Distinction**:  \n   The term \"cell phone\" emphasizes the technology behind mobile communication, whereas \"mobile phone\" is a broader term that simply refers to the device's portability.\n\nIn summary, \"cell phone\" highlights the cellular network architecture, while \"mobile phone\" refers to the device's mobility. Both terms are widely used interchangeably today.",
